Newly generated NestJS project by @nestia/migrate would form like above.At first, every controllers would be generated following URL path hierarchy. Also, typia.random<T>() function would be utilized in every route methods to generate random data following specific response DTO type. SDK library and Mockup simulator also utilize the typia.random<T>() function too.As you can see from above example case, @nestia/migrate perfectly revives every DTO types and route methods, but it doesn't revive business logics. It means that, you have to implement business logics by yourself. Of course, it's not a matter if you're utilizing @nestia/migrate not for real NestJS migration, but for generating SDK library and Mockup simulator only.

